sndctl - Sound Engine Control

SYNOPSIS
  sndctl play "MML"     Start BGM (non-blocking)
  sndctl stop           Stop BGM
  sndctl status         Show playback status
  sndctl se <id>        Play sound effect
  sndctl mute           Master mute
  sndctl unmute         Master unmute

DESCRIPTION
  Control the OS32 background sound engine.
  BGM plays in the background using the timer
  interrupt (100Hz), allowing other programs
  to execute simultaneously.

  SE (sound effects) temporarily borrow FM Ch2
  or SSG ChC from BGM. After SE finishes, BGM
  resumes on that channel automatically.

MML SYNTAX
  T120   Tempo (BPM)
  O4     Octave (1-8)
  L4     Default note length (4=quarter)
  A-G    Notes (+/# for sharp)
  R      Rest
  > <    Octave up/down
  [...]  Loop
  @C0    Channel (0-2=FM, 3-5=SSG)
  @T0    Tone number

SE IDS
  0: Cursor   1: Select   2: Cancel
  3: Error    4: Coin     5: Beep

EXAMPLES
  sndctl play "T120 O4 L4 [CDEFGAB>C<]"
  sndctl se 1
  sndctl stop
